    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "Four new species of Polycirrus Grube, 1850 (Polychaeta: Terebellidae) from Campos Basin, southeastern Brazil" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218716>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218717>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218722> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218716>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Polycirrus nonatoi sp. nov. Holotype (MZUSP 1213). A, anterior end, ventral view; B, D, anterior end, right dorso-lateral views; C, anterior end, left ventro-lateral view; E, notochaetae, segment 6; F, G, uncini, anterior and posterior neuropodia, respectively. Numbers refer to segments; ul = upper lip; P * = basal part of prostomium; plp = prostomial lateral processes; vlp = ventro-lateral pads. Scale bars: A – C = 200 µm; D = 500 µm; E – F = 20 μm; G = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/218716/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218717>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Polycirrus nonatoi sp. nov. Paratype 10 (MZUSP 1243). A, anterior end, ventral view; B, anterior end, left lateral view; C, anterior end, dorsal view; D, closer view of the anterior end, ventral view; E, close up view of the oral area, ventral view; F, posterior end, frontal view; G, anterior notopodia; arrows point to post-chaetal notopodial lobes; H, anterior segments, right lateral view; arrows point to nephridial and genital papillae; I, anterior notopodium; arrows point to post-chaetal notopodial lobes. Numbers refer to segments; ll = lower lip; P * = basal part of prostomium; P (dp) = distal part of prostomium; plp = prostomial lateral processes; ul = upper lip. Scale bars: A = 300 μm; B – E = 200 μm; F – H = 100 μm; I = 50 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/218717/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218722>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Polycirrus breviuncinatus sp. nov. Holotype (MZUSP 1220). A, entire worm; B, anterior end, ventral view; C, anterior end, dorsal view; D, anterior end, left lateral view; E, notochaetae, segment 8; F, uncinus, segment 18. Numbers refer to segments; ll = lower lip; P * = basal part of the prostomium; P (dp) = distal part of the prostomium; ul = upper lip. Scale bars: A = 500 µm; B – D = 150 µm; E = 20 µm; F = 5 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/218722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

